BT 1 0 0 1 0 21.8555 Tm 7.875 TL /F1 5.25 Tf 0 0 0 rg (Security Enhanced LInux \(SELinux\) is an additional layer of security that defines which processes can access which files, directories, ports etc. Definions of access rights are defined in policies as a set of) Tj T* (rules. SELinux is a Linux Security Module \(LSM\) that is built into the Linux kernel. If it is enabled it can run in enforcing or permissive state. Permissive is like a monitor-only mode that allows access, but still) Tj T* (reports to ) Tj /F4 5.25 Tf (/var/log/audit/audit.log) Tj /F1 5.25 Tf (. Permissive mode is used when troubleshooting. State is defined under ) Tj /F4 5.25 Tf (/etc/selinux/config) Tj /F1 5.25 Tf (. SELinux uses auditd deamon for recording events.) Tj T* ET
