BT 1 0 0 1 0 45.4805 Tm 7.875 TL /F1 5.25 Tf 0 0 0 rg (Key terminology: - Context: Label used to focus on security properties - Remember: SELinux policy checked after DAC, so for example 755 checked first - Context has several fields: user, role, type and) Tj T* (security level - Type is the most important, as system resource <) Tj (> process interaction uses mostly this and not whole context - Type end with _t \(examples: http_port_t for ports, http_sys_content_t for) Tj T* (/var/www/html, tmp_t for /var/tmp\) - AVC: SELinux Denial Event \(Access Vector Cache\) - ausearch: Parses audit logs - sealert: RHEL, integrates with setroubleshootd to translate AVC to human readable) Tj T* (translation - audit2allow: Creates a SELinux policy that can be loaded, but should check labeling problem first - Common would be using non-standard directory for a service, e.g. srv/web1 instead of) Tj T* (/var/www/html - .pp files are compiled selinux policy filed - .te are uncompiled/readable selinux policies - semanage: Add context \(labels\) to dirs/files/procs/ports - restorecon: Apply changes defined via) Tj T* (semanage - matchpathcon: Check context of file path and compare to default label - semodule: Manage custom policy \(install module, deinstall module\) - sesearch: Search SELinux policy) Tj T* ET
